# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share this.
#   For Emi-Mower, we can keep or ignore it depending on team preferences,
#   but usually it's fine to check in if we want to lock python version.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if lock is tool-specific, it may be ignored.
#   We use uv lock, so we definitely keep uv.lock tracked.

# Poetry
#   Poetry uses poetry.lock, which we track.

# pdm
#   PDM uses pdm.lock, which we track.

